
[1]devoutly

   DEVOUTLY, adv.

   1. With solemn attention and reverence to God; with ardent devotion.

   He was devoutly engaged in prayer.

   2. Piously; religiously; with pious thoughts; as, he viewed the cross
   devoutly.

   3. Sincerely; solemnly; earnestly; as, a consummation devoutly to be
   wished.
